Vendored, CGO-free PIV protocol layer
=====================================

The files in this directory (except pcsc_goscard.go, NOTICE, and the *_test.go
files authored by TestifySec) are vendored verbatim from the go-piv/piv-go
project:

    Upstream:  github.com/go-piv/piv-go/v2
    Version:   v2.5.0
    License:   Apache License 2.0
    Copyright: Copyright 2020 Google LLC (and contributors)

Files vendored UNCHANGED (logic), retaining their original Apache-2.0 headers:

    piv.go          PIV applet select, version/serial, PIN/PUK/mgmt-key auth
    key.go          keygen, sign (GENERAL AUTHENTICATE), attest, cert get/store,
                    crypto.Signer / crypto.Decrypter implementations
    pcsc.go         apdu type, SW-code error mapping (apduErr/AuthErr/ErrNotFound),
                    the cgo-free (*scTx).Transmit command-chaining wrapper
    pcsc_errors.go  SCARD_* return-code -> message table
    doc.go          package doc
    certs/          Yubico attestation CA roots/intermediates (//go:embed inputs)

NOTE: piv.go and pcsc.go were normalized with `gofmt` for the current Go
toolchain (whitespace/comment-indentation only). All other vendored files are
byte-identical to upstream, with two logic deviations in piv.go:

  - (*client).Open: upstream v2.5.0 leaks the PC/SC handle and context when
    h.Begin() fails, and leaks the handle+context (closing only tx) when
    ykSelectApplication() fails. Because the connection is SCardShareExclusive,
    a leaked handle keeps the reader/card locked for the process and breaks
    retries. Both error paths now close everything they opened.

  - (*YubiKey).Close: upstream v2.5.0 disconnects the handle and releases the
    context but never ends the PC/SC transaction Open() started with h.Begin().
    On stacks that require SCardEndTransaction before SCardDisconnect this can
    leave the exclusive transaction/card locked on the normal close path
    (Card.Close / cardBoundSigner.Close). Close now ends the transaction first,
    then the handle and context, preserving the first non-nil error.

    Both fixes are marked "DEVIATION from upstream go-piv v2.5.0" inline. No
    copyright headers were modified.

Files NOT vendored (they carry the cgo PC/SC bindings) and DELETED relative to
upstream:

    pcsc_unix.go, pcsc_darwin.go, pcsc_linux.go, pcsc_freebsd.go,
    pcsc_openbsd.go, pcsc_windows.go

These are replaced by pcsc_goscard.go (Copyright 2026 TestifySec, Inc.), a pure-Go
(CGO_ENABLED=0) PC/SC transport backed by github.com/ElMostafaIdrassi/goscard
(which drives PC/SC over github.com/ebitengine/purego — no `import "C"`). The
struct types (scContext/scHandle/scTx), their method signatures, the rcSuccess
constant, and scCheck are kept compatible with the upstream cgo transport so the
vendored protocol files compile and run unchanged.

The go-piv/piv-go/v2 module is still a (direct) dependency of this package, but
ONLY for its cgo-free third_party/rsa subpackage (an RSA-PSS fork used by
key.go). Importing that subpackage does not compile any cgo file.

